when you blush.

722
01:05:16,003 --> 01:05:18,382
Like a wild flower.

723
01:05:18,422 --> 01:05:21,762
It's my dyspepsia.

724
01:05:23,432 --> 01:05:24,472
Morning, all.

725
01:05:26,012 --> 01:05:27,222
Beautiful day.

726
01:05:46,281 --> 01:05:48,031
Pack of Gitanes, please.

727
01:05:48,071 --> 01:05:52,001
Bravo! Vive la France! You scalded me.

728
01:05:52,041 --> 01:05:56,461
Bravo! Ten out of ten! Bull's-eye!

729
01:06:00,461 --> 01:06:02,631
It was Amélie. She...

730
01:06:36,619 --> 01:06:40,629
Do you know what happened
when they went up Mont Blanc?

731
01:06:40,669 --> 01:06:43,129
The silicon in her face froze up.

732
01:06:43,169 --> 01:06:47,679
Her face was a festering mass!

733
01:07:13,538 --> 01:07:17,328
Mulled wine and ginger biscuits.

734
01:07:18,368 --> 01:07:20,038
Thank you.

735
01:07:20,078 --> 01:07:23,288
I was too hard the other day
on the girl with the glass.

736
01:07:24,338 --> 01:07:28,298
Tell me about that boy she saw.
Did they meet again?

737
01:07:29,837 --> 01:07:30,887
No.

738
01:07:32,097 --> 01:07:33,757
They're into different things.

739
01:07:34,807 --> 01:07:37,387
Luck is like the Tour de France.

740
01:07:37,427 --> 01:07:39,517
You wait, and it flashes past you.

741
01:07:41,097 --> 01:07:45,067
You have to catch it while you can.

742
01:08:09,466 --> 01:08:11,216
Can I help you?

743
01:08:11,256 --> 01:08:14,426
Excuse me.
I found this album in the street and I...

744
01:08:14,466 --> 01:08:19,056
Nino will be so pleased!
He was so sad the other day.

745
01:08:19,096 --> 01:08:21,055
I almost prayed to St Anthony.

746
01:08:22,595 --> 01:08:24,805
Is... Nino there?

747
01:08:24,855 --> 01:08:27,645
No. On Wednesdays he works at the funfair.

748
01:08:29,985 --> 01:08:32,065
How long has he had this collection?

749
01:08:32,105 --> 01:08:36,575
Since I got him the job here, last year.

750
01:08:36,615 --> 01:08:40,825
Before, he collected footprints.
He worked nights.

751
01:08:40,865 --> 01:08:46,834
In the daytime
he took pictures of footprints in wet cement.

752
01:08:46,874 --> 01:08:49,044
He's a funny guy.

753
01:08:49,084 --> 01:08:51,374
When we met, he was a Santa Claus.

754
01:08:54,544 --> 01:08:56,294
Other things like...

755
01:08:56,344 --> 01:09:00,214
Whenever he heard a funny
laugh, he'd tape it.

756
01:09:04,394 --> 01:09:05,434
Really?

757
01:09:07,264 --> 01:09:09,894
Must be hard for his girlfriend.

758
01:09:09,934 --> 01:09:12,274
He never keeps them long.

759
01:09:12,314 --> 01:09:15,103
Times are hard for dreamers.

760
01:09:15,153 --> 01:09:17,943
Eva! Where are those coffees?

761
01:09:17,983 --> 01:09:20,443
I'd better go. Thanks for the album.

762
01:09:20,493 --> 01:09:24,163
It's OK. I've got time to
take it to the funfair.

763
01:09:24,203 --> 01:09:28,663
Suit yourself. The ghost train.
Ask for Nino Quincampoix, like the street.

764
01:09:52,932 --> 01:09:55,062
I'm looking for Nino. Is he here?

765
01:09:55,102 --> 01:09:57,192
He doesn't get off till seven.

766
01:09:58,732 --> 01:10:01,152
- Is there no way to see him before?
- Sure.

767
01:10:02,492 --> 01:10:04,072
20 francs.

768
01:11:15,019 --> 01:11:16,639
See you next Wednesday.

769
01:11:28,318 --> 01:11:32,778
5pm tomorrow, Montmartre carousel
near the phone box. Bring a 5 franc piece.

770
01:11:50,887 --> 01:11:53,007
Want to know about her?

771
01:11:55,637 --> 01:11:58,477
- You know her? You saw her?
- You bet.

772
01:11:58,557 --> 01:12:00,517
She put us in her shirt pocket.

773
01:12:01,597 --> 01:12:03,147
Next to her breast.

774
01:12:03,227 --> 01:12:05,107
Is she pretty?

775
01:12:05,187 --> 01:12:07,107
Not bad.

776
01:12:08,187 --> 01:12:10,197
- Beautiful.
- No, pretty.

777
01:12:10,277 --> 01:12:11,567
- Beautiful.
- Pretty.

778
01:12:11,657 --> 01:12:15,447
- What does she want from you?
- She's broke.

779
01:12:15,526 --> 01:12:18,196
She wants a reward for the album.

780
01:12:18,286 --> 01:12:20,536
Or she collects photos, too.

781
01:12:20,616 --> 01:12:24,916
She wants to trade us
for a one-eyed man with glasses!

782
01:12:29,586 --> 01:12:30,586
No, you dope!

783
01:12:32,176 --> 01:12:34,506
She's in love.

784
01:12:34,596 --> 01:12:37,346
- I don't even know her.
- Yes, you do.

785
01:12:37,386 --> 01:12:39,176
Since when?

786
01:12:39,266 --> 01:12:40,976
You've always known her.

787
01:12:41,056 --> 01:12:42,305
In your dreams.

788
01:12:55,275 --> 01:12:56,825
Hello?

789
01:12:56,905 --> 01:13:00,955
Yes. You! Man with the
plastic bag! It's for you.

790
01:13:02,535 --> 01:13:03,995
- Me?
- Yes.

791
01:13:07,335 --> 01:13:08,334
Thank you.

792
01:13:10,334 --> 01:13:11,334
Hello?

793
01:13:11,414 --> 01:13:14,174
Follow the blue arrows, Mr. Quincampoix.

794
01:14:39,461 --> 01:14:43,921
When the finger's pointing to the sky,
only a fool looks at the finger.

795
01:15:56,448 --> 01:15:57,448
Hello?

796
01:15:58,538 --> 01:16:00,868
I know the stranger in the pictures.

797
01:16:00,918 --> 01:16:04,998
He's a ghost. He's invisible,
Mr. Quincampoix.

798
01:16:05,048 --> 01:16:08,418
He only appears when the film is developed.

799
01:16:08,468 --> 01:16:11,837
When a girl has her photo taken,

800
01:16:11,887 --> 01:16:17,847
he goes "Oooh!" in her ear,
while he gently caresses her neck.

801
01:16:17,887 --> 01:16:20,437
That's how he got caught, Mr. Quincampoix.

802
01:16:24,187 --> 01:16:25,477
Who are you?

803
01:16:25,517 --> 01:16:26,977
Page 51.

804
01:16:35,577 --> 01:16:37,156
[DO YOU

805
01:16:37,196 --> 01:16:39,036
WANT

806
01:16:39,076 --> 01:16:41,536
TO MEET ME?]

807
01:18:19,543 --> 01:18:22,382
Listen to this. "A boy of six,

808
01:18:22,422 --> 01:18:24,592
while his parents sleep, drives off

809
01:18:24,632 --> 01:18:26,392
in a pedal car.

810
01:18:26,432 --> 01:18:30,142
Found on a motorway
near Münster in Germany,

811
01:18:30,182 --> 01:18:33,772
he told the police he
wanted to see the stars."

812
01:18:33,812 --> 01:18:37,482
Isn't life beautiful, eh?

813
01:18:37,522 --> 01:18:42,112
Love. The only bug she hadn't caught!

814
01:18:42,152 --> 01:18:45,202
- Nobody's immune.
- At least it gives me a break.

815
01:18:45,242 --> 01:18:47,451
Love's a great beautician.

816
01:18:49,661 --> 01:18:53,121
What's she like? Tall? Small? Blonde? Dark?

817
01:18:55,541 --> 01:18:57,621
Let's say... average height.

818
01:18:58,881 --> 01:19:01,921
Not a dwarf or a giraffe. Normal.

819
01:19:03,301 --> 01:19:05,551
Pretty, for her type.

820
01:19:05,591 --> 01:19:07,931
As for blonde or dark...

821
01:19:09,511 --> 01:19:12,601
...it's hard to say,
but she wasn't a redhead.

822
01:19:12,641 --> 01:19:14,520
- Unless...
- Forget it.

823
01:19:15,640 --> 01:19:20,520
I do remember she casually asked
if you had a girlfriend.

824
01:19:20,560 --> 01:19:21,610
And?

825
01:19:21,650 --> 01:19:24,110
I said you weren't interested, right?

826
01:19:25,530 --> 01:19:27,030
You didn't!

827
01:19:27,070 --> 01:19:29,320
What do you care? You don't even know her.

828
01:19:30,370 --> 01:19:34,580
- Exactly. It's the mystery.
- You won't find mystery here.

829
01:19:34,620 --> 01:19:36,830
A pound of nectarines, please.

830
01:19:36,870 --> 01:19:39,709
These ones here are the prettiest.

831
01:19:39,749 --> 01:19:41,879
Trust him. He's an artist!

832
01:19:41,919 --> 01:19:45,009
He's been going home every night
with tons of unsold stock.

833
01:19:45,049 --> 01:19:48,219
What for? Is he stewing a pig?

834
01:19:48,259 --> 01:19:50,429
No, sir! He's studying art!

835
01:19:50,469 --> 01:19:54,179
He sells leeks all day long
and paints turnips all night!

836
01:19:54,219 --> 01:19:56,309
The boy's a useless vegetable.

837
01:19:56,349 --> 01:19:57,849
A good prompter

838
01:19:57,889 --> 01:20:01,479
in each cellar window
whispering cutting retorts

839
01:20:01,519 --> 01:20:04,149
would mean shy people had the last laugh.

840
01:20:04,189 --> 01:20:06,648
At least you'll never be a vegetable.

841
01:20:06,688 --> 01:20:08,948
Even artichokes

842
01:20:08,988 --> 01:20:10,028
have hearts.

843
01:20:13,028 --> 01:20:16,658
You'll never be a vegetable.
Even artichokes have hearts!

844
01:20:58,076 --> 01:20:59,696
Memory seven.

845
01:21:17,386 --> 01:21:21,636
Darling Mado,
I miss you more and more each day.

846
01:21:21,686 --> 01:21:24,975
I'm an exile in a world of dreary khaki.

847
01:21:25,015 --> 01:21:27,315
I can't sleep, can't eat...

848
01:21:27,355 --> 01:21:30,065
This camp was the biggest mistake of my life,

849
01:21:30,105 --> 01:21:33,905
depriving me of my beloved
for five long weeks.

850
01:21:33,945 --> 01:21:36,825
I think of you endlessly. Your Adrien.

851
01:21:38,575 --> 01:21:43,365
I turned down my last month's wages
instead of giving notice.

852
01:21:44,415 --> 01:21:47,745
I dream of better times ahead.

853
01:21:47,785 --> 01:21:51,794
An orange-colored day. Remember, my love?

854
01:21:51,834 --> 01:21:53,924
Your ever-loving Adrien.

855
01:21:55,714 --> 01:21:57,134
Good news, darling Mado.

856
01:21:57,174 --> 01:22:00,514
Soon I'll be able to afford a car

857
01:22:00,554 --> 01:22:03,054
and drive home every night.

858
01:22:03,094 --> 01:22:07,514
Till then, meet me on
Friday and we'll go out.

859
01:24:54,467 --> 01:24:56,677
[MOTHER]

860
01:24:59,517 --> 01:25:01,597
Psychiatric Helpline.

861
01:25:03,147 --> 01:25:05,227
Hello? Hello?

862
01:25:33,966 --> 01:25:36,426
[WHERE & WHEN?]

863
01:25:46,145 --> 01:25:48,605
One hour later at 11 Boulevard St Martin,

864
01:25:48,645 --> 01:25:52,275
Amélie walks into a party goods
and costume shop.

865
01:25:53,315 --> 01:25:57,775
At the same time,
a man leaves his home at 108 Rue Lecourbe.

866
01:25:59,735 --> 01:26:03,495
26 minutes later, Amélie is at the
photo booth at the Gare de l'Est.

867
01:26:07,745 --> 01:26:11,834
Simultaneously,
the man in red shoes parks outside.

868
01:26:11,874 --> 01:26:15,254
The time is exactly 11:40.

869
01:27:00,923 --> 01:27:02,962
At this precise moment,

870
01:27:03,052 --> 01:27:07,762
only Amélie has the key
to the riddle of the mystery man.

871
01:27:12,682 --> 01:27:14,352
How's it going, Mrs. Wells?

872
01:27:14,432 --> 01:27:17,272
It's always better when it's not raining.

873
01:27:17,312 --> 01:27:19,732
- This is for you.
- Me?

874
01:27:29,701 --> 01:27:33,371
Dear Mrs. Wells,
We recently recovered a mailbag

875
01:27:33,451 --> 01:27:35,501
that was lost in a plane crash

876
01:27:35,581 --> 01:27:39,211
on October 12th 1969 on Mont Blanc.

877
01:27:39,291 --> 01:27:43,751
We are forwarding the enclosed letter
to your address.

878
01:27:43,801 --> 01:27:47,931
Please accept our apologies
for the uncustomary delay.

879
01:27:48,011 --> 01:27:50,681
Jacques Grosjean, Customer Services.

880
01:27:52,051 --> 01:27:56,350
Darling Mado, I'm in exile.
I can't sleep, can't eat.

881
01:27:56,390 --> 01:27:58,100
I think of you endlessly.

882
01:27:58,190 --> 01:28:02,020
I know I've made
the biggest mistake of my life.

883
01:28:02,110 --> 01:28:04,780
I turned down that woman's money.

884
01:28:04,860 --> 01:28:09,780
If all goes well,
I'll soon be able to afford a house.

885
01:28:09,860 --> 01:28:12,870
I dream of better times ahead

886
01:28:12,950 --> 01:28:16,790
when you'll forgive me and join me here

887
01:28:16,870 --> 01:28:20,210
one orange-colored day.
Your ever-loving Adrien.

888
01:28:50,068 --> 01:28:52,198
Mr. Dufayel, another package for you.

889
01:29:02,038 --> 01:29:05,288
Mr. Dufayel, do you know
what happened to the concierge?

890
01:29:06,708 --> 01:29:08,048
She got a letter.

891
01:29:09,088 --> 01:29:11,928
From her husband. 40 years late.

892
01:29:14,257 --> 01:29:16,307
That's a lot, isn't it, Mr. Dufayel?

893
01:29:29,567 --> 01:29:32,987
I'm not big on still life, Mr. Dufayel.

894
01:29:33,067 --> 01:29:36,077
Then work on your thin layer.

895
01:29:36,117 --> 01:29:38,867
Fat over thin. Always!

896
01:29:57,716 --> 01:29:59,516
- Mr. Dufayel...
- Yes!

897
01:29:59,556 --> 01:30:03,936
The papers said
that there'll soon be a new star.

898
01:30:03,976 --> 01:30:11,105
- So you're into stars now?
- I saw it on TV at my mum's, that's why.

899
01:30:12,945 --> 01:30:14,695
I don't know if it's true.

900
01:30:14,735 --> 01:30:17,025
In America

901
01:30:17,115 --> 01:30:20,405
they're going to take all
the rich people's ashes,

902
01:30:20,445 --> 01:30:23,115
put them in a satellite

903
01:30:23,155 --> 01:30:25,455
and shoot it into space.

904
01:30:25,535 --> 01:30:27,915
The satellite's going to shine forever.

905
01:30:32,544 --> 01:30:34,084
And Lady Di...

906
01:30:34,124 --> 01:30:36,384
Will they do the same for her?

907
01:30:36,424 --> 01:30:37,424
Lady Di, Lady Di!

908
01:30:37,504 --> 01:30:38,754
Give it a rest!

909
01:30:38,794 --> 01:30:41,554
I can't concentrate.

910
01:30:43,724 --> 01:30:44,724
Lady Di!

911
01:30:45,844 --> 01:30:46,844
Lady Di!

912
01:30:48,104 --> 01:30:49,144
Renoir.

913
01:32:30,450 --> 01:32:31,490
Morning, sir.

914
01:32:48,219 --> 01:32:49,259
Cambodia.

915
01:32:54,849 --> 01:32:56,599
I don't understand.

916
01:32:56,639 --> 01:33:00,519
Brilliant! You couldn't have done better.

917
01:33:00,559 --> 01:33:03,769
- Did it work?
- It's getting there.

918
01:33:03,809 --> 01:33:06,729
Ask me again any time. The harm's done.

919
01:33:06,779 --> 01:33:10,448
- What do you mean?
- Everybody calls me Snow White!

920
01:34:16,176 --> 01:34:19,006
[The Two Windmills café from 4pm.]

921
01:34:25,516 --> 01:34:27,435
- Eva?
- Yes?

922
01:34:27,475 --> 01:34:31,225
Could you stand in for me at four?

923
01:34:31,275 --> 01:34:33,195
Again?

924
01:34:36,525 --> 01:34:37,985
Close the door!

925
01:34:40,155 --> 01:34:42,155
What's up with him?

926
01:34:42,195 --> 01:34:43,955
Is he sulking?

927
01:34:43,995 --> 01:34:47,575
- He thinks I smile too much.
- He'd rather you frowned?

928
01:34:47,625 --> 01:34:50,545
With other men, yes.

929
01:34:53,254 --> 01:34:57,674
Nino is late. Amélie can only think
of two possible explanations.

930
01:34:57,714 --> 01:34:59,804
Firstly, that he didn't find the photo.

931
01:35:01,634 --> 01:35:04,094
Secondly, before he could assemble it,

932
01:35:04,134 --> 01:35:08,434
a gang of bank robbers took him hostage.

933
01:35:08,474 --> 01:35:10,474
The cops gave chase.

934
01:35:10,514 --> 01:35:12,314
They got away,

935
01:35:12,354 --> 01:35:15,104
but he caused a crash.

936
01:35:15,144 --> 01:35:17,354
When he came to,

937
01:35:17,404 --> 01:35:19,063
he'd lost his memory,

938
01:35:20,943 --> 01:35:22,823
An ex-con picked him up,

939
01:35:22,863 --> 01:35:27,073
mistook him for a fugitive,
and shipped him to Istanbul.

940
01:35:28,033 --> 01:35:30,283
He met some Afghan raiders,

941
01:35:30,333 --> 01:35:33,913
who took him to steal
some Russian warheads.

942
01:35:37,543 --> 01:35:41,383
But their truck hit a mine
at the border with Tajikistan.

943
01:35:41,423 --> 01:35:46,932
He survived, took to the hills,
and became a Mujaheddin.

944
01:35:46,972 --> 01:35:49,932
Amélie refuses to get upset for a guy

945
01:35:49,972 --> 01:35:54,562
who'll eat borscht all his life
in a hat like a tea cosy.

946
01:36:13,791 --> 01:36:16,001
- What can I get you?
- A coffee, please.

947
01:36:17,081 --> 01:36:18,961
A coffee.

948
01:36:40,980 --> 01:36:42,440
Here's your coffee.

949
01:36:43,980 --> 01:36:45,030
Thank you.

950
01:37:08,719 --> 01:37:11,049
[Today's menu]

951
01:37:20,059 --> 01:37:21,519
He's understood.

952
01:37:21,559 --> 01:37:24,769
He's going to put his teaspoon down,

953
01:37:26,189 --> 01:37:29,778
dip his finger in the sugar,

954
01:37:34,528 --> 01:37:37,238
turn around slowly,

955
01:37:37,288 --> 01:37:39,368
and speak to me.

956
01:37:44,958 --> 01:37:46,958
Excuse me.

957
01:37:48,458 --> 01:37:49,708
Is this you?

958
01:37:56,177 --> 01:37:57,427
Yes, it's you.

959
01:38:18,117 --> 01:38:20,197
I'll take that.

960
01:38:22,616 --> 01:38:24,286
Another coffee?

961
01:38:24,326 --> 01:38:26,456
- No, thanks. I'm fine.
- OK.

962
01:38:47,016 --> 01:38:51,475
So it's this man here,
the one with his hand up?

963
01:38:52,735 --> 01:38:53,775
Yes.

964
01:38:56,105 --> 01:38:58,985
Is she in love with him?

965
01:39:01,785 --> 01:39:02,825
Yes.

966
01:39:04,745 --> 01:39:08,125
I think it's time she took a real risk.

967
01:39:08,165 --> 01:39:12,665
She might just do that.
She's devising a stratagem.

968
01:39:12,705 --> 01:39:16,374
She's fond of stratagems.

969
01:39:18,424 --> 01:39:19,464
Yes.

970
01:39:21,174 --> 01:39:23,304
In fact, she's cowardly.

971
01:39:24,674 --> 01:39:28,054
That's why I can't capture her look.

972
01:39:29,894 --> 01:39:35,394
Dufayel's attempts to meddle are intolerable!

973
01:39:37,904 --> 01:39:43,863
If Amélie chooses to live in a dream

974
01:39:43,903 --> 01:39:48,113
and remain an introverted young woman,

975
01:39:48,163 --> 01:39:52,833
she has an absolute right
to mess up her life!

976
01:40:27,572 --> 01:40:29,322
What are you doing, Mr. Dufayel?

977
01:40:31,702 --> 01:40:33,831
Tell me, Lucien.

978
01:40:33,871 --> 01:40:38,751
For deliveries,
do you keep keys to all the apartments?

979
01:40:51,221 --> 01:40:55,101
One of your booths is out of order.

980
01:40:57,231 --> 01:40:59,770
It seems to be jammed.

981
01:41:00,900 --> 01:41:03,190
Gare de l'Est ticket hall.

982
01:41:06,030 --> 01:41:08,400
- Buy a video, get one free.
- No, thanks.

983
01:41:15,160 --> 01:41:16,830
Sam?

984
01:41:17,870 --> 01:41:18,910
Samantha?

985
01:41:22,250 --> 01:41:23,290
Samantha?

986
01:41:28,209 --> 01:41:30,129
Can you stand in for me at...

987
01:41:52,608 --> 01:41:56,238
Photo booth, Gare de l'Est ticket hall,
Tuesday 5pm.

988
01:41:56,328 --> 01:41:59,618
[Can you stand in for me this afternoon?]

989
01:43:10,895 --> 01:43:12,185
Almost done.

990
01:43:17,365 --> 01:43:21,405
The mystery man wasn't a ghost
or a man scared of ageing,

991
01:43:21,445 --> 01:43:23,495
but simply the repairman,

992
01:43:23,575 --> 01:43:26,035
a normal guy doing his job.

993
01:43:28,165 --> 01:43:29,785
Sorry.

994
01:44:15,453 --> 01:44:18,793
He keeps spying on me!
It's making me sick.

995
01:44:18,873 --> 01:44:22,293
4:05: Blatant female conspiracy.

996
01:44:23,343 --> 01:44:26,763
Gosh, you're tense, Georgette!

997
01:44:27,842 --> 01:44:29,392
Good luck. You'll need it.

998
01:44:34,812 --> 01:44:39,352
Excuse me. Did you put this in my pocket?

999
01:44:39,442 --> 01:44:42,862
- Yes, but I'm not the one...
- I know. Where is she?

1000
01:44:42,902 --> 01:44:44,442
She's at her father's.

1001
01:44:44,482 --> 01:44:49,912
It's awkward. I'd like to speak to
you, but... I finish work at six.

1002
01:44:49,952 --> 01:44:51,912
- Can you come back?
- OK.

1003
01:44:52,952 --> 01:44:54,031
See you later.

1004
01:44:54,081 --> 01:44:57,661
4:08: Docking scheduled.

1005
01:45:29,490 --> 01:45:34,160
The blond guy in a camel coat.
He's very absent-minded, too.

1006
01:45:34,200 --> 01:45:35,950
How come?

1007
01:45:36,990 --> 01:45:39,460
He came back three times the same afternoon.

1008
01:45:40,710 --> 01:45:41,960
1:12:

1009
01:45:42,040 --> 01:45:43,290
Camel coat.

1010
01:45:43,380 --> 01:45:44,630
2:50:

1011
01:45:44,670 --> 01:45:46,499
Camel coat.

1012
01:45:46,549 --> 01:45:48,759
- 4:17: Camel coat.
- Stop it!

1013
01:45:49,799 --> 01:45:53,009
My rash has come back! Look, Suzanne!

1014
01:45:53,049 --> 01:45:56,759
My rash is back. He's driving me nuts.

1015
01:45:56,809 --> 01:45:58,969
Lay off!

1016
01:45:59,019 --> 01:46:03,309
If she had a clear conscience,
she wouldn't be in such a state.

1017
01:46:03,349 --> 01:46:05,309
I've had it. I'm going home.

1018
01:46:05,359 --> 01:46:08,859
Psychos are the last straw!

1019
01:46:10,239 --> 01:46:12,278
Georgette! Georg...

1020
01:46:13,858 --> 01:46:16,618
Stop smothering them!
Women need to breathe.

1021
01:46:16,658 --> 01:46:19,948
You let them breathe,
they want a change of air.

1022
01:46:19,998 --> 01:46:21,868
Fresh air's healthy.

1023
01:46:21,908 --> 01:46:23,918
Shut it, failure!

1024
01:46:26,458 --> 01:46:28,168
Failed writer, failed life...

1025
01:46:28,208 --> 01:46:30,798
I love the word "fail".

1026
01:46:30,838 --> 01:46:32,878
Failure is human destiny.

1027
01:46:32,928 --> 01:46:34,508
It's gasbag time!

1028
01:46:34,548 --> 01:46:37,807
Failure teaches us that life is but a draft,

1029
01:46:37,847 --> 01:46:41,727
a long rehearsal for a
show that will never play.

1030
01:46:43,137 --> 01:46:45,477
I bet he stole that.

1031
01:46:45,517 --> 01:46:48,017
I do have some original ideas,

1032
01:46:48,067 --> 01:46:53,527
but people always steal them.
A bit like your women.

1033
01:46:53,567 --> 01:46:55,607
Meaning?

1034
01:46:55,657 --> 01:46:58,867
Meaning you'd better get used to it.

1035
01:46:58,907 --> 01:47:01,447
Speak for yourself, you...

1036
01:47:01,497 --> 01:47:02,537
What?

1037
01:47:06,286 --> 01:47:09,416
- What's going on?
- Nothing much. Georgette went out.

1038
01:47:09,456 --> 01:47:11,206
Joseph got mad.

1039
01:47:11,256 --> 01:47:12,756
"Went out?"

1040
01:47:12,796 --> 01:47:18,006
Just like Gina. You know who's she's with?
The guy with the plastic bag.

1041
01:47:19,716 --> 01:47:22,096
I saw their little game.

1042
01:47:22,136 --> 01:47:24,476
The note in the coat pocket,

1043
01:47:24,516 --> 01:47:26,146
4:08.

1044
01:47:26,186 --> 01:47:30,145
Back he comes, and hey presto!
Out they go.

1045
01:47:34,065 --> 01:47:37,735
- I'm worried for Amélie because I like you.
- What do you mean?

1046
01:47:38,775 --> 01:47:42,575
By and large, the men I like
are mentally unsound.

1047
01:47:42,615 --> 01:47:45,655
- I'd like to know more about you.
- Ask me questions.

1048
01:47:48,455 --> 01:47:50,245
One swallow doesn't make...?

1049
01:47:51,335 --> 01:47:52,375
A swallow?

1050
01:47:53,955 --> 01:47:55,505
A summer.

1051
01:47:55,545 --> 01:47:56,924
And clothes...?

1052
01:47:56,964 --> 01:47:58,504
The man.

1053
01:47:58,544 --> 01:47:59,964
- A good cat deserves...?
- A rat.

1054
01:48:00,004 --> 01:48:01,674
- Patience...?
- Is a virtue.

1055
01:48:01,714 --> 01:48:03,304
- Rolling stone...?
- Gathers no moss.

1056
01:48:03,344 --> 01:48:05,674
- It's a sin...?
- To steal a pin.

1057
01:48:05,724 --> 01:48:07,724
Absence makes...?

1058
01:48:07,764 --> 01:48:09,224
The heart grow fonder.

1059
01:48:09,264 --> 01:48:11,264
- Not bad.
- You collect them?

1060
01:48:11,314 --> 01:48:15,644
In my family, we say a man
who knows his proverbs can't be all bad.

1061
01:48:20,234 --> 01:48:23,693
Pretty girl from the 5th
floor, listen to this!

1062
01:48:23,733 --> 01:48:26,703
- Do you believe in miracles?
- Not today.

1063
01:48:28,113 --> 01:48:30,283
You're in for a surprise.

1064
01:48:30,323 --> 01:48:33,663
What if I told you that a team of climbers

1065
01:48:33,703 --> 01:48:37,663
on Mont Blanc had found

1066
01:48:37,713 --> 01:48:42,343
hard proof that my husband loved me?

1067
01:49:15,701 --> 01:49:17,831
Lucien, I need some yeast.

1068
01:49:17,871 --> 01:49:21,791
For Miss Amélie?
She's baking her famous plum cake?

1069
01:49:21,831 --> 01:49:24,801
Collignon! Go and get the yeast.

1070
01:50:18,969 --> 01:50:20,599
Amélie?

1071
01:50:20,639 --> 01:50:21,689
Amélie?

1072
01:50:29,029 --> 01:50:30,069
Amélie?

1073
01:50:51,918 --> 01:50:52,968
[I'll be back]

1074
01:51:24,037 --> 01:51:27,036
Go into the bedroom, Miss Poulain.

1075
01:51:43,096 --> 01:51:46,226
So, little Amélie,

1076
01:51:46,266 --> 01:51:50,356
your bones aren't made of glass.

1077
01:51:50,396 --> 01:51:53,525
You can take life's knocks.

1078
01:51:53,565 --> 01:51:57,945
If you let this chance go by,

1079
01:51:57,985 --> 01:52:04,655
eventually your heart will become

1080
01:52:04,695 --> 01:52:10,745
as dry and brittle as my skeleton.

1081
01:52:12,375 --> 01:52:13,915
So...

1082
01:52:13,955 --> 01:52:17,124
Go and get him, for pete's sake!

1083
01:55:04,618 --> 01:55:10,458
[Without you, today's emotions
would be the scurf of yesterday's]

1084
01:56:06,766 --> 01:56:08,476
International airport.

1085
01:56:08,516 --> 01:56:13,565
September 28th 1997. It is exactly 11am.

1086
01:56:13,605 --> 01:56:16,315
At the funfair, near the ghost train,

1087
01:56:16,355 --> 01:56:19,525
the marshmallow twister is twisting.

1088
01:56:19,565 --> 01:56:21,865
Meanwhile, on a bench in Villette Square,

1089
01:56:21,905 --> 01:56:27,365
Félix Lerbier learns there are more links
in his brain than atoms in the universe.

1090
01:56:28,455 --> 01:56:29,575
Meanwhile,

1091
01:56:29,625 --> 01:56:33,295
at the Sacré Cœur,
the nuns are practicing their backhand.

1092
01:56:33,375 --> 01:56:35,755
The temperature is 24°C,

1093
01:56:35,795 --> 01:56:37,675
humidity 70%,

1094
01:56:37,715 --> 01:56:40,964
atmospheric pressure 999 millibars.
